<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Vibe Check - CURSED Programming Language</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles/docs.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Outfit:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <h1><span class="gradient-text">ud83dude31 Vibe Check ud83dude31</span></h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Switch up your code's mood, literally!</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        <div class="doc-grid">
            <aside class="sidebar">
                <nav>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="basic-types.html">Basic Types</a></li>
                        <li><a href="functions.html">Functions</a></li>
                        <li><a href="if-else.html">If-Else</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#" class="active">Vibe Check</a></li>
                        <li><a href="loops.html">Loops</a></li>
                        <li><a href="error-handling.html">Error Handling</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </nav>
            </aside>

            <article class="content">
                <section class="intro">
                    <div class="tag-container">
                        <span class="tag">Control Flow</span>
                        <span class="tag">Core Syntax</span>
                        <span class="tag">Literally Fire</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="lead">The <code>vibe_check</code> statement is CURSED's take on the switch/case pattern - it's giving main character energy to your conditional logic!</p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>u2728 The Basic Vibe u2728</h2>
                    <p>A <code>vibe_check</code> lets you evaluate an expression and execute different code blocks based on matching values. It's like if-else chains but way more aesthetic.</p>
                    
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <div class="code-title">basic_vibe_check.csd</div>
                        <pre><code>slay checkDayVibe(day tea) {
    vibe_check day {
        mood "Monday":
            console.print("Monday blues fr fr");
        mood "Friday":
            console.print("Weekend vibes loading...");
        basic:  // This is the default case
            console.print("Just another day, bestie");
    }
}</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>ud83dudd25 Vibe Check Anatomy ud83dudd25</h2>
                    
                    <div class="feature-grid">
                        <div class="feature-card">
                            <h3>The Expression</h3>
                            <p>After <code>vibe_check</code>, you provide the expression to evaluate.</p>
                            <code>vibe_check statusCode {</code>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="feature-card">
                            <h3>Mood Cases</h3>
                            <p>Each case starts with <code>mood</code> followed by the value(s) to match.</p>
                            <code>mood 200:</code>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="feature-card">
                            <h3>The Basic Mood</h3>
                            <p>The default case is labeled <code>basic</code> (like "basic behavior" when no mood matches).</p>
                            <code>basic:</code>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="feature-card">
                            <h3>Ghosting</h3>
                            <p>Use <code>ghosted;</code> to prevent fallthrough (like <code>break</code> in other languages).</p>
                            <code>ghosted;</code>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="info-box">
                    <h3>u26a0ufe0f Vibe Check Rules u26a0ufe0f</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Default Fallthrough:</strong> Unlike many languages, CURSED <em>automatically</em> falls through to the next case unless you add <code>ghosted;</code></li>
                        <li><strong>Expression Types:</strong> Can check strings, integers, and other comparable values</li>
                        <li><strong>Multiple Values:</strong> A single mood can match multiple values with commas: <code>mood 1, 2, 3:</code></li>
                        <li><strong>Basic Case:</strong> The <code>basic</code> case is optional but usually a good idea</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>ud83dudc8e Multiple Value Matching ud83dudc8e</h2>
                    <p>When you want to handle multiple values with the same code, separate them with commas:</p>
                    
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <div class="code-title">multiple_moods.csd</div>
                        <pre><code>slay rateYourFit(score normie) tea {
    sus verdict tea;
    
    vibe_check score {
        mood 8, 9, 10:
            verdict = "Slaying so hard rn";
        mood 5, 6, 7:
            verdict = "Mid, but go off I guess";
        mood 2, 3, 4:
            verdict = "It's giving 2007 vibes, ngl";
        basic:
            verdict = "Not the serve bestie";
    }
    
    yolo verdict;
}</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>ud83dudc7b Ghosting to Control Flow ud83dudc7b</h2>
                    <p>By default, execution falls through to the next case after finishing the current one. Use <code>ghosted;</code> to exit the vibe check after a case:</p>
                    
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <div class="code-title">ghosted_example.csd</div>
                        <pre><code>slay weekdayVibe(day tea) {
    vibe_check day {
        mood "Monday":
            console.print("New week, who dis?");
            // Falls through to Tuesday's case!
        mood "Tuesday":
            console.print("Taco Tuesday vibes");
            ghosted;  // Exits the vibe_check here
        mood "Wednesday":
            console.print("Halfway there!");
            ghosted;
        basic:
            console.print("Just vibing");
    }
}</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>ud83dudcab Advanced Vibes ud83dudcab</h2>
                    <p>You can get creative with vibe checks to handle more complex scenarios:</p>
                    
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <div class="code-title">nested_vibes.csd</div>
                        <pre><code>slay processHttpResponse(status normie, body tea) {
    vibe_check status {
        mood 200, 201, 202:
            console.print("Success, bestie!");
            
            // Nested vibe check
            vibe_check body.length {
                mood 0:
                    console.print("Empty response, kinda sus");
                    ghosted;
                basic:
                    console.print("Got data: " + body);
            }
            ghosted;
            
        mood 400, 401, 403:
            console.print("That's not giving valid user energy");
            ghosted;
            
        mood 500, 502, 503:
            console.print("Server's not in its era rn");
            ghosted;
            
        basic:
            console.print("Unexpected status: " + status);
    }
}</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="tips">
                    <h2>Bestie Advice ud83dudc8e</h2>
                    <div class="tips-grid">
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <div class="tip-icon">ud83dudcad</div>
                            <h3>Mind the Fallthrough</h3>
                            <p>Remember that CURSED automatically falls through cases! Add <code>ghosted;</code> liberally to avoid unexpected behavior.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <div class="tip-icon">ud83dudca1</div>
                            <h3>Group Similar Cases</h3>
                            <p>Put related moods together to take advantage of fallthrough when it makes sense.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <div class="tip-icon">ud83dudc40</div>
                            <h3>Default is Your Friend</h3>
                            <p>Always include a <code>basic</code> case to handle unexpected values and avoid the vibe check equivalent of null pointer exceptions.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tip-card">
                            <div class="tip-icon">ud83dudccc</div>
                            <h3>Keep It Clean</h3>
                            <p>If your vibe check has many cases or complex logic in each case, consider breaking it into separate functions.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="next-steps">
                    <h2>Where To Next?</h2>
